Drama shows

 True Detective 2014-Present In True Detective, performances by Woody Harrelsen and Matthew McConaughey reel the viewer in, while the style, vision and direction make it hard to turn away. Mindhunter 2017-Present Mindhunter distinguishes itself in a crowded genre with ambitiously cinematic visuals and a meticulous attention to character development. Netflix has since decided to discontinue production of Mindhunter for unknown reasons House of Cards 2013-2018 Bolstered by strong performances -- especially from Kevin Spacey -- and surehanded direction, House of Cards is a slick, engrossing drama that may redefine how television is produced. {/*Second row of three card images on the page*/} The Sopranos 1999-2007 The Sopranos smartly runs an emotional gamut, offering detailed character work and riveting suspense while displaying a flair for both comedy and drama. The Wire 2002-2008 Though it takes its time getting started, The Wire is worth the wait, spinning a connective web of characters and delivering no-holds-barred commentary on some of America's unsettling societal problems. Mad Men 2007-2015 Oozing evocative early 1960s ambiance, Mad Men is a sly, subversive look at the American workplace that radiates class, wit, and an undercurrent of disaffection.
